questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application running on Tomcat experiences a slow, continuous memory leak leading to an `OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space` after 48 hours. Upon analyzing the heap dump, you discover thousands of instances of `byte[]` retained by thread-local maps. The application uses the following class to store contextual transactional metadata:

java
@Component
public class TransactionContextHolder {
    private static final ThreadLocal<byte[]> context = new ThreadLocal<>();

    public void setContext(byte[] data) {
        context.set(data);
    }

    public byte[] getContext() {
        return context.get();
    }

    @Transactional
    public void clear() {
        context.remove();
    }
}


This component is invoked from a standard `@RestController` to store and retrieve data within the request lifecycle.
